<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,411,868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,807,832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">DISCUSSION:</emphasis>
Based on our collections, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zhiltzova" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[700,782,808,832]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Capnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[700,782,808,832]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Capnia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are relatively common in 
<collectingCountry box="[1101,1210,807,831]" name="Mongolia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
compared to other capniids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
